From 9c0005234ee4ca54da84c3a38d9854a13db096c0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: poeggi <48416618+poeggi@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 09:27:17 +0400
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] test: add unit tests for gen_uuid_v5_mac (KAT vectors,
 format, canary, determinism)

test/test_utils.c: four known-answer test vectors verified against Python
  uuid.uuid5(DNS_NAMESPACE, 'mac:xx:xx:xx:xx:xx:xx'), plus output format
  checks (length 36, hyphens, lowercase hex, version nibble '5', RFC 4122
  variant bits), buffer canary, and determinism test.

test/mbedtls/{sha1,base64}.h + test/stubs.c: minimal stub headers and
  empty implementations so the test binary compiles without any crypto
  library installed (utils.c hash_uuid5_* helpers are self-contained).

Build with: make test  (uses native host cc, no cross-compiler needed)
---
